---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageTitle = "About Me";

const skills = ["Julia","Stata","Matlab","R", "Python", "Fortran","Astro"];


const identity = {
  firstName: "Cristi√°n",
  lastName:"Valencia",
  nationality: "Chilean",
  countryLive: "USA",
  university: "Washington University in St. Louis",
  occupation: "PhD Student in Economics",
  hobbies: ["photography", "Baking", "Reading"],
};
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>

  <p>Here are a few facts about me:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>My name is {identity.firstName} {identity.lastName}.</li>
    <li>I am a {identity.occupation} from {identity.university}.</li>
    {identity.hobbies.length >= 2 && (
      <li>Two of my hobbies are: {identity.hobbies[0]} and {identity.hobbies[1]}</li>
    )}
  </ul>
<p>Currently, I feel comfortable, in a scale from best to worst, using the following programming languages/software/frameworks:</p>
  <ul>
    {skills.map((skill) => (
      <li class="skill">{skill}</li>
    ))}
  </ul>
  
</BaseLayout>